# ~/.config/cmux/usage-sentinels.env
#
# The poller no longer stores workspace ids: cmux 0.64.15 removed stable
# workspace UUIDs, so each sentinel is resolved fresh every run by its TITLE
# LABEL (the workspace whose title starts with "5h "/"7d "). This file only
# carries OPTIONAL label overrides — the defaults below work out of the box, so
# an empty file (or no file at all) is fine.
#
# Setup is just: create two idle workspaces and rename them so their titles
# start with the labels, e.g.
#   cmux workspace list                                    # find the refs
#   cmux rename-workspace --workspace workspace:<N> "5h"   # then the same for 7d
# The poller then keeps the rest of each title (bar, %, reset) updated.
#
# SENTINEL_5H_LABEL=5h
# SENTINEL_7D_LABEL=7d
